  "description": "¶Entry conditions You should already know the definition of a group and be comfortable with the idea of inverses.\n¶Definitions A subgroup HH of a group GG is a subset H⊆GH \\subseteq G that is itself a group under the same operation. Equivalently, HH is a subgroup if and only if HH is non-empty, closed under the group operation, and closed under inverses.\nGiven a subgroup H≤GH \\leq G and an element g∈Gg \\in G, the left coset of HH by gg is gH={g⋅h∣h∈H}gH = \\{g \\cdot h \\mid h \\in H\\}. Right cosets HgHg are defined analogously.\n",
  "name": "Subgroups and Cosets",
